<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.1//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml11/DTD/xhtml11.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
 <head>
  <title>CSS3 Test: @page border-width property physical units</title>
  <link rel="author" title="Tom Clancy" href="mailto:tclancy@revenution.com"/>
  <link rel="help" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/css3-page/#page-properties"/>
  <link rel="help" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/css3-page/#page-box-page-rule"/>
  <meta name="flags" content="paged" />
  <meta name="assert" content="A border declaration within the @page context applies to the page box."/>
  <style type="text/css"><![CDATA[
   @page  { 
		border-color: aqua;
		border-style: solid;
		border-width: 2cm 4cm 0 1cm;
	}
  ]]></style>
 </head>
 <body>
  <div>When printed, this page must have an aqua border which is thin (1cm) on the left, thicker on top (2cm) and thickest on the right (4cm). No border should appear on the bottom.</div>
 </body>
</html>